owner_cmnt: This year has been simultaneously one of the best and worst years of my life. I have been given the opportunity of travel & to start a business venture I am passionate about. But I also lost my father after he passed away earlier this year. I decided to take what I have dubbed the _‹€Lea Michele_‹_ approach to grief after being inspired by something she said in an interview about her own tragic loss - "at one point that there is an empowerment that comes with grief. At some point you find it. It's very hard, but you will find it._‹ù I_‹_m not going to lie and say there hasn_‹_t been some hard days and there has certainly been a lot of soul searching. What I have learned is there is always going to be highs and lows in life. It doesn_‹_t need to be grief necessarily, but sadness, confusion or just road blocks that make you want to give up. Don_‹_t give up. You never know who is watching how you handle your own trial as the inspiration on how to get through theirs. So don_‹_t stop, don_‹_t give in because they may never get to start if you do. You can_‹_t control what comes to you, but you can control what comes through you. As with anything tough that comes your way - you can choose to fall, or you can choose to rise. All you can do is your best and hopefully make a positive impact through your choices & actions. Whatever it is you're going through, you can get through it. _éê‰"
